title: Shuttler Wei Feng earns spot in main draw of French Open Super Series
text:
Shuttler Wei Feng earns spot in main draw of French Open Super Series Wednesday October 21, 2015 Print Article 
Wei Feng to meet Japanese veteran Sho Sasaki today. — Reuters file pic KUALA LUMPUR, Oct 21 — National men’s shuttler Chong Wei Feng booked a spot in the main draw of the 2015 French Open Super Series Badminton Tournament after crossing two hurdles in the qualifying round at the Stade Pierre de Coubertin in Paris. 
In the first qualifying match yesterday, Wei Feng beat Christian Lind Thomsen of Denmark 21-10, 21-9 before overcoming Raul Must of Estonia 21-11, 21-11, Badminton World Federation (BWF) website; www.bwfbadminton.org reported. 
Wei Feng will meet Japanese veteran Sho Sasaki today. 
Men’s doubles pair Hoon Thien How/Lim Khim Wah had to give a walkover to French pair Gregor Dunikowski/Thom Gicquel after Thien How suffered an injury. 
Malaysia’s top women’s singles player Tee Jing Yi will take on Delphine Lansac from the host country in the final qualifying match later today. 
Jing Yi defeated Schafer Rong of the United States 24-22, 21-11 while Delphine edged Denmark’s Anna Thea Madsen 21-19, 17-21, 21-17. 
Former world number one Datuk Lee Chong Wei and a number of other Malaysian shuttlers will kick off their campaign in the opening round of the tournament today. — Bernama
